expression - package expression
 
Expression - Class in expression
An Expression is a tree which encapsulates arbitrary mathematical functions according to a specific grammar.
Expression(double) - Constructor for class expression.Expression
Builds an Expression that consists of a single real number.
Expression(char) - Constructor for class expression.Expression
Builds an Expression that consists of a variable.
Expression(Expression, char, Expression) - Constructor for class expression.Expression
A binary tree of Expressions.
ExpressionCopier - Class in expression
Tools for copying Expressions, especially deep copies.
ExpressionCopier() - Constructor for class expression.ExpressionCopier
 
expressionToString(Expression) - Static method in interface transpile.Transpiler
An intermediary helper function which transforms an Expression into a general arithmetic form that many languages are happy to parse.
ExpressionType - Enum in expression
An enum outlining the three different types of Expression.

The three types are as follows:

Number: A real number.
Ex: f(x) = 2

Variable: A variable function.
